{
  "texts": [
    "We selected the 539 most recent notes from 355 patients for manual annotation.",
    "Demographic characteristics of the 355 patients can be found in Supplementary Table S5.",
    "Of the 539 manually annotated notes, the most common type of note were progress notes (216) followed by ED provider notes (102) and telephone encounters (38) (Supplementary Table S6).",
    "Of the 182 patients that were identified as having current or past housing instability, only 18% (33 patients) had a structured SNOMED code related to housing instability in their chart (Table 1).",
    "Although the percentage of patients with structured codes for HI is low, it is higher than what has been previously reported, and it is well known that structured fields do not adequately capture a patient's housing status 29, 35."
  ]
}